[2026-03-09T15:17:31Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01W9kuSs3FekS6k9reoakznX","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a complete picture. Let me create a comprehensive summary document:\n\n## Summary: Run Logs Display in Cloche Codebase\n\nBased on my thorough investigation of the codebase, here's how run logs are displayed and managed in Cloche:\n\n### 1. Web Handler for Run Logs/History\n**File**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`\n\nThe main handler is `handleRunDetail()` (line 376-403) which:\n- Retrieves run metadata from `RunStore`\n- Fetches step execution captures from `CaptureStore`\n- Renders the `run_detail.html` template with run state and steps\n- Merges captured step executions into display entries\n\nAdditional log-specific endpoints:\n- `GET /api/runs/{id}/stream` (line 716-775): Server-Sent Events (SSE) endpoint for live log streaming\n- `GET /api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output` (line 563-634): Retrieve individual step output logs\n- `GET /runs/{id}` (line 376): HTML page for run detail view\n\n### 2. HTML Template for Rendering Logs\n**File**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html`\n\nKey features:\n- **Live log viewer** (lines 62-66): A `<div id=\"log-viewer\">` that streams logs in real-time\n- **Steps table** (lines 34-60): Shows step name, result, start time, and duration\n- **Log streaming script** (lines 70-237):\n  - Connects via `EventSource('/api/runs/{id}/stream')` for SSE\n  - Parses JSON log lines with format: `{timestamp, type, content}`\n  - Appends log lines to the log viewer with syntax highlighting per type\n  - Auto-scrolls to bottom as logs arrive\n  - Toggle-able step output rows showing per-step logs\n\nLog line format in UI: `[timestamp] [type] content`\n- Types: `\"status\"`, `\"script\"`, `\"llm\"`\n\n### 3. Log Data Storage and Retrieval\n\n#### **RunStore Interface** (`/workspace/internal/ports/store.go` lines 10-18)\nStores run metadata:\n- `CreateRun()`, `GetRun()`, `UpdateRun()`, `DeleteRun()`\n- `ListRuns()`, `ListRunsByProject()`\n- `ListProjects()`\n\n#### **CaptureStore Interface** (`/workspace/internal/ports/store.go` lines 20-23)\nStores step execution events:\n```go\ntype CaptureStore interface {\n    SaveCapture(ctx context.Context, runID string, exec *domain.StepExecution) error\n    GetCaptures(ctx context.Context, runID string) ([]*domain.StepExecution, error)\n}\n```\n\n#### **LogStore Interface** (`/workspace/internal/ports/store.go` lines 25-40)\nFast index for log files:\n```go\ntype LogStore interface {\n    SaveLogFile(ctx context.Context, entry *LogFileEntry) error\n    GetLogFiles(ctx context.Context, runID string) ([]*LogFileEntry, error)\n    GetLogFilesByStep(ctx context.Context, runID, stepName string) ([]*LogFileEntry, error)\n    GetLogFileByType(ctx context.Context, runID, fileType string) ([]*LogFileEntry, error)\n}\n```\n\n#### **SQLite Implementation** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go`)\n- **runs table**: Stores run metadata including state, timestamps, container ID\n- **step_executions table**: Stores step start/completion with results\n- **log_files table** (lines 87-96): \n  - Index of log file paths by type (full, script, llm)\n  - Columns: `id, run_id, step_name, file_type, file_path, file_size, created_at`\n\n### 4. Log Parsing and Formatting Logic\n\n#### **Log Format** (`/workspace/internal/logstream/logstream.go`)\nRaw log format in `full.log`:\n```\n[2026-03-03T10:15:00Z] [status] step_started: build\n[2026-03-03T10:15:01Z] [script] npm run build\n[2026-03-03T10:15:02Z] [llm] Claude: Starting analysis\n```\n\nLog types (EntryType):\n- `TypeStatus` = \"status\" (workflow events)\n- `TypeScript` = \"script\" (shell command output)\n- `TypeLLM` = \"llm\" (Claude Code agent output)\n\n#### **Log Parsing in Handler** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` lines 777-814)\n- Regex pattern: `^\\[([^\\]]+)\\] \\[([^\\]]+)\\] (.*)$` (line 778)\n- Parses timestamp, type, and content from full.log lines\n- Falls back to \"script\" type for unparseable lines\n\n#### **Log Streaming** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`)\nFor completed runs:\n- `streamFullLog()` (line 781-797): Reads archived full.log, parses lines, sends via SSE\n- Uses `parseFullLogLine()` (line 800-813) to convert raw log lines to JSON\n\n### 5. Raw JSON Log Entry Format from Claude Code\n\n**Protocol Format** (`/workspace/internal/protocol/status.go`):\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"log|step_started|step_completed|run_completed|error\",\n  \"step_name\": \"step_name\",\n  \"message\": \"log message content\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-03-03T10:15:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\nKey protocol messages:\n- `MsgLog`: Direct log output from agent (type=\"llm\")\n- `MsgStepStarted`: Step execution starts\n- `MsgStepCompleted`: Step execution completes with result\n- `MsgRunCompleted`: Workflow completes\n- `MsgError`: Error messages\n\n### 6. Live Log Streaming Architecture\n\n#### **Broadcaster** (`/workspace/internal/logstream/broadcaster.go`)\n- In-memory pub/sub system for active runs\n- Fans out `LogLine` structs to multiple subscribers\n- Non-blocking (drops lines if subscriber buffer full)\n- Marked as done when run completes\n\n#### **gRPC Server** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` lines 218-226)\nReceives status messages from container:\n```go\nif s.logBroadcast != nil {\n    s.logBroadcast.Publish(runID, logstream.LogLine{\n        Timestamp: msg.Timestamp.Format(time.RFC3339),\n        Type:      \"llm\",\n        Content:   msg.Message,\n    })\n}\n```\n\n#### **Log File Indexing** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` lines 704-757)\nAfter container execution:\n- Extracts output directory to `.cloche/{runID}/output/`\n- Indexes all `.log` files by type:\n  - `full.log` → type=\"full\"\n  - `llm-{stepname}.log` → type=\"llm\"\n  - `{stepname}.log` → type=\"script\"\n  - `container.log` → internal only\n- Creates database entries in `log_files` table for fast lookup\n\n### 7. File Paths and Storage Structure\n\n**Run output directory**: `{projectDir}/.cloche/{runID}/output/`\n\n**Log files created during execution**:\n- `full.log`: Complete unified log with all types\n- `{stepname}.log`: Per-step output (script or agent intermediate)\n- `llm-{stepname}.log`: Copy of agent step output for easy retrieval\n- `container.log`: Full Docker container stdout/stderr\n\n### 8. Step Output Retrieval (`handler.go` lines 563-634)\n\nLookup precedence:\n1. Check LogStore index by step name (`GetLogFilesByStep()`)\n2. Try LLM-specific log if type=\"llm\" (`llm-{step}.log`)\n3. Try per-step output (`{step}.log`)\n4. Fall back to container log (`container.log`)\n5. Last resort: Live Docker logs from running container\n\n### Summary of Files\n\n**Critical implementation files**:\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` - Web handlers for logs\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html` - Log UI\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go` - Database persistence\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` - Log publishing and extraction\n- `/workspace/internal/logstream/logstream.go` - Log writer\n- `/workspace/internal/logstream/broadcaster.go` - Live streaming\n- `/workspace/internal/protocol/status.go` - Status message format\n- `/workspace/internal/agent/runner.go` - In-container logging\n- `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go` - Interface definitions"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: afaf4374e829be319 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 76756\ntool_uses: 41\nduration_ms: 70729</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"34e205ce-686a-450f-bced-2ed6d70cc0e4","uuid":"8898137e-f3ef-4bf1-b8b4-f0299e0941ab","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Find how run logs are displayed in this codebase. Look for:\n1. The web handler that serves run logs/history\n2. The HTML template that renders logs\n3. How log data is stored and retrieved (RunStore, CaptureStore interfaces)\n4. Any existing log parsing logic\n5. The format of the raw JSON log entries from Claude Code\n\nSearch thoroughly in internal/adapters/web/, internal/adapters/, internal/domain/, internal/ports/, and cmd/ directories.","agentId":"afaf4374e829be319","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a complete picture. Let me create a comprehensive summary document:\n\n## Summary: Run Logs Display in Cloche Codebase\n\nBased on my thorough investigation of the codebase, here's how run logs are displayed and managed in Cloche:\n\n### 1. Web Handler for Run Logs/History\n**File**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`\n\nThe main handler is `handleRunDetail()` (line 376-403) which:\n- Retrieves run metadata from `RunStore`\n- Fetches step execution captures from `CaptureStore`\n- Renders the `run_detail.html` template with run state and steps\n- Merges captured step executions into display entries\n\nAdditional log-specific endpoints:\n- `GET /api/runs/{id}/stream` (line 716-775): Server-Sent Events (SSE) endpoint for live log streaming\n- `GET /api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output` (line 563-634): Retrieve individual step output logs\n- `GET /runs/{id}` (line 376): HTML page for run detail view\n\n### 2. HTML Template for Rendering Logs\n**File**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html`\n\nKey features:\n- **Live log viewer** (lines 62-66): A `<div id=\"log-viewer\">` that streams logs in real-time\n- **Steps table** (lines 34-60): Shows step name, result, start time, and duration\n- **Log streaming script** (lines 70-237):\n  - Connects via `EventSource('/api/runs/{id}/stream')` for SSE\n  - Parses JSON log lines with format: `{timestamp, type, content}`\n  - Appends log lines to the log viewer with syntax highlighting per type\n  - Auto-scrolls to bottom as logs arrive\n  - Toggle-able step output rows showing per-step logs\n\nLog line format in UI: `[timestamp] [type] content`\n- Types: `\"status\"`, `\"script\"`, `\"llm\"`\n\n### 3. Log Data Storage and Retrieval\n\n#### **RunStore Interface** (`/workspace/internal/ports/store.go` lines 10-18)\nStores run metadata:\n- `CreateRun()`, `GetRun()`, `UpdateRun()`, `DeleteRun()`\n- `ListRuns()`, `ListRunsByProject()`\n- `ListProjects()`\n\n#### **CaptureStore Interface** (`/workspace/internal/ports/store.go` lines 20-23)\nStores step execution events:\n```go\ntype CaptureStore interface {\n    SaveCapture(ctx context.Context, runID string, exec *domain.StepExecution) error\n    GetCaptures(ctx context.Context, runID string) ([]*domain.StepExecution, error)\n}\n```\n\n#### **LogStore Interface** (`/workspace/internal/ports/store.go` lines 25-40)\nFast index for log files:\n```go\ntype LogStore interface {\n    SaveLogFile(ctx context.Context, entry *LogFileEntry) error\n    GetLogFiles(ctx context.Context, runID string) ([]*LogFileEntry, error)\n    GetLogFilesByStep(ctx context.Context, runID, stepName string) ([]*LogFileEntry, error)\n    GetLogFileByType(ctx context.Context, runID, fileType string) ([]*LogFileEntry, error)\n}\n```\n\n#### **SQLite Implementation** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go`)\n- **runs table**: Stores run metadata including state, timestamps, container ID\n- **step_executions table**: Stores step start/completion with results\n- **log_files table** (lines 87-96): \n  - Index of log file paths by type (full, script, llm)\n  - Columns: `id, run_id, step_name, file_type, file_path, file_size, created_at`\n\n### 4. Log Parsing and Formatting Logic\n\n#### **Log Format** (`/workspace/internal/logstream/logstream.go`)\nRaw log format in `full.log`:\n```\n[2026-03-03T10:15:00Z] [status] step_started: build\n[2026-03-03T10:15:01Z] [script] npm run build\n[2026-03-03T10:15:02Z] [llm] Claude: Starting analysis\n```\n\nLog types (EntryType):\n- `TypeStatus` = \"status\" (workflow events)\n- `TypeScript` = \"script\" (shell command output)\n- `TypeLLM` = \"llm\" (Claude Code agent output)\n\n#### **Log Parsing in Handler** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` lines 777-814)\n- Regex pattern: `^\\[([^\\]]+)\\] \\[([^\\]]+)\\] (.*)$` (line 778)\n- Parses timestamp, type, and content from full.log lines\n- Falls back to \"script\" type for unparseable lines\n\n#### **Log Streaming** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`)\nFor completed runs:\n- `streamFullLog()` (line 781-797): Reads archived full.log, parses lines, sends via SSE\n- Uses `parseFullLogLine()` (line 800-813) to convert raw log lines to JSON\n\n### 5. Raw JSON Log Entry Format from Claude Code\n\n**Protocol Format** (`/workspace/internal/protocol/status.go`):\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"log|step_started|step_completed|run_completed|error\",\n  \"step_name\": \"step_name\",\n  \"message\": \"log message content\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-03-03T10:15:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\nKey protocol messages:\n- `MsgLog`: Direct log output from agent (type=\"llm\")\n- `MsgStepStarted`: Step execution starts\n- `MsgStepCompleted`: Step execution completes with result\n- `MsgRunCompleted`: Workflow completes\n- `MsgError`: Error messages\n\n### 6. Live Log Streaming Architecture\n\n#### **Broadcaster** (`/workspace/internal/logstream/broadcaster.go`)\n- In-memory pub/sub system for active runs\n- Fans out `LogLine` structs to multiple subscribers\n- Non-blocking (drops lines if subscriber buffer full)\n- Marked as done when run completes\n\n#### **gRPC Server** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` lines 218-226)\nReceives status messages from container:\n```go\nif s.logBroadcast != nil {\n    s.logBroadcast.Publish(runID, logstream.LogLine{\n        Timestamp: msg.Timestamp.Format(time.RFC3339),\n        Type:      \"llm\",\n        Content:   msg.Message,\n    })\n}\n```\n\n#### **Log File Indexing** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` lines 704-757)\nAfter container execution:\n- Extracts output directory to `.cloche/{runID}/output/`\n- Indexes all `.log` files by type:\n  - `full.log` → type=\"full\"\n  - `llm-{stepname}.log` → type=\"llm\"\n  - `{stepname}.log` → type=\"script\"\n  - `container.log` → internal only\n- Creates database entries in `log_files` table for fast lookup\n\n### 7. File Paths and Storage Structure\n\n**Run output directory**: `{projectDir}/.cloche/{runID}/output/`\n\n**Log files created during execution**:\n- `full.log`: Complete unified log with all types\n- `{stepname}.log`: Per-step output (script or agent intermediate)\n- `llm-{stepname}.log`: Copy of agent step output for easy retrieval\n- `container.log`: Full Docker container stdout/stderr\n\n### 8. Step Output Retrieval (`handler.go` lines 563-634)\n\nLookup precedence:\n1. Check LogStore index by step name (`GetLogFilesByStep()`)\n2. Try LLM-specific log if type=\"llm\" (`llm-{step}.log`)\n3. Try per-step output (`{step}.log`)\n4. Fall back to container log (`container.log`)\n5. Last resort: Live Docker logs from running container\n\n### Summary of Files\n\n**Critical implementation files**:\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` - Web handlers for logs\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html` - Log UI\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go` - Database persistence\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` - Log publishing and extraction\n- `/workspace/internal/logstream/logstream.go` - Log writer\n- `/workspace/internal/logstream/broadcaster.go` - Live streaming\n- `/workspace/internal/protocol/status.go` - Status message format\n- `/workspace/internal/agent/runner.go` - In-container logging\n- `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go` - Interface definitions"}],"totalDurationMs":70729,"totalTokens":76756,"totalToolUseCount":41,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5322,"cache_read_input_tokens":69229,"output_tokens":2205,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":5322},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
