ng `handleAPIStepOutput` endpoint. I can detect LLM logs by the `type` query parameter and transform the content on the fly without touching storage. text, I should handle the full stream-json format properly—checking for both `text_delta` events and `result` fields to extract all the content Claude generates. I'll auto-detect whether content is stream-json by checking if the first line parses as valid JSON with recognized event types, then parse accordingly or return the raw output unchanged. Writing the parser...","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5216,"cache_read_input_tokens":28953,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":5216},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"34e205ce-686a-450f-bced-2ed6d70cc0e4","uuid":"9c18b6f5-6284-4705-ad3b-e1f2ebb09aa6"}
