[2026-03-09T15:19:58Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01YA5fCikpVs5e6CmMWS3Awo","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a complete picture. Let me create a comprehensive report of all code related to displaying run logs and history.\n\n## Summary of Log Display Code in Cloche\n\nI've thoroughly searched the codebase for all code related to displaying run logs and history. Here's a complete breakdown:\n\n### 1. **Log Storage and Retrieval**\n\n#### Log Writing/Persistence:\n- **File**: `/workspace/internal/logstream/logstream.go`\n  - `Writer` struct with `Log()` method writes timestamped, type-prefixed log entries to `.cloche/output/full.log`\n  - Format: `[timestamp] [type] content` (one entry per line)\n  - Supports three entry types: `TypeStatus`, `TypeScript`, `TypeLLM`\n  - Thread-safe with mutex locks\n\n#### Log Storage Interface and Implementation:\n- **Ports** (`/workspace/internal/ports/store.go`):\n  - `LogStore` interface with methods:\n    - `SaveLogFile()` - indexes a log file entry\n    - `GetLogFiles()` - retrieves all log files for a run\n    - `GetLogFilesByStep()` - retrieves logs for a specific step\n    - `GetLogFileByType()` - retrieves logs of a specific type (full/script/llm)\n  - `LogFileEntry` struct with fields: ID, RunID, StepName, FileType, FilePath, FileSize, CreatedAt\n\n- **Implementation** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go`):\n  - SQLite database with `log_files` table\n  - `SaveLogFile()` at line 301 - inserts into log_files table\n  - `GetLogFiles()` at line 311 - queries all logs for a run\n  - `GetLogFilesByStep()` at line 322 - queries logs by run and step name\n  - `GetLogFileByType()` at line 333 - queries logs by type\n  - Helper function `scanLogFiles()` at line 344 parses query results\n\n#### Log File Indexing:\n- **gRPC Server** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`, lines 704-757):\n  - `indexLogFiles()` function scans output directory after run completes\n  - Categorizes files:\n    - `full.log` → fileType=\"full\" (complete unified log)\n    - `llm-*.log` → fileType=\"llm\" (Claude Code output)\n    - `<step>.log` → fileType=\"script\" (script/command output)\n    - `container.log` is skipped (internal use only)\n  - Creates index entries for database persistence\n\n### 2. **Log Parsing**\n\n- **File**: `/workspace/internal/logparse/parse.go`\n  - `FormatStreamJSON()` - converts raw Claude Code stream-json output to human-readable text\n  - Parses event types: `content_block_start`, `content_block_delta`, `content_block_stop`, `message_stop`, `result`\n  - Extracts text content and tool names from stream\n  - `IsStreamJSON()` - detects if content is Claude Code stream-json format\n  - Returns original if parsing fails (graceful fallback)\n\n### 3. **Web UI Display**\n\n#### Log Streaming for Active Runs:\n- **Broadcaster** (`/workspace/internal/logstream/broadcaster.go`):\n  - `Broadcaster` struct manages real-time log distribution\n  - `Subscribe()` - clients subscribe to a run's log stream\n  - `Publish()` - broadcasts LogLine to all subscribers with non-blocking delivery\n  - `Finish()` - closes all subscriber channels when run completes\n  - `LogLine` struct: Timestamp, Type, Content\n\n#### Handler Functions (`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`):\n\n1. **handleAPIStream** (lines 721-780):\n   - Server-Sent Events (SSE) endpoint at `/api/runs/{id}/stream`\n   - For active runs: subscribes to logBroadcast and streams live updates\n   - For completed runs: reads archived full.log file\n   - Sends \"done\" event with final run state\n\n2. **streamFullLog** (lines 786-802):\n   - Reads `.cloche/{runID}/output/full.log` line by line\n   - Parses \"[timestamp] [type] content\" format via regex\n   - Converts to LogLine JSON and sends as SSE events\n\n3. **parseFullLogLine** (lines 805-819):\n   - Regex: `^\\[([^\\]]+)\\] \\[([^\\]]+)\\] (.*)$`\n   - Extracts timestamp, type, content from full.log lines\n\n4. **handleAPIStepOutput** (lines 564-639):\n   - JSON endpoint at `/api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output`\n   - Retrieves step-specific logs with optional filtering by type\n   - Priority: log index → file path conventions → live docker logs\n   - Calls `logparse.FormatStreamJSON()` unless format=raw\n   - Log file lookup order:\n     - `{outputDir}/llm-{step}.log` (if type==\"llm\")\n     - `{outputDir}/{step}.log` (per-step output)\n     - `{outputDir}/container.log` (fallback)\n     - Live Docker logs from container if still running\n\n#### Templates (`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/`):\n\n1. **run_detail.html** (lines 1-238):\n   - Log viewer section: `<div id=\"log-viewer\">` with pre-formatted content\n   - Step execution table with clickable rows\n   - Real-time log status badge showing \"Live\" or \"Complete\"\n   - JavaScript:\n     - Connects to SSE stream at `/api/runs/{runID}/stream`\n     - `appendLogLine()` - adds log entries to DOM with type-based CSS classes\n     - Auto-scroll enabled while at bottom; disabled when scrolled up\n     - Poll updates for steps every 2 seconds during active runs\n     - Click handlers for expandable step output rows\n     - Fetches step output from `/api/runs/{runID}/steps/{step}/output`\n\n2. **runs.html** (lines 1-106):\n   - Lists all runs with state, workflow, started/completed times\n   - Truncated error messages (80 chars)\n   - Project filter dropdown\n   - Polls `/api/runs` every 3 seconds for updates\n\n3. **layout.html** and **projects.html**:\n   - Mini run history (recent dots with color-coded states)\n   - Project health indicators\n\n### 4. **CLI Log Display**\n\n#### Command: `cloche logs` (`/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go`, lines 223-304):\n\n- Subcommand: `logs <run-id> [--step <name>] [--type <full|script|llm>] [--follow]`\n- **Without --follow**: \n  - Calls gRPC `StreamLogs()` RPC\n  - Streams LogEntry messages\n  - Handles types: \"step_started\", \"step_completed\", \"run_completed\", \"full_log\", \"*_log\"\n- **With --follow** (`cmdLogsFollow`, lines 306-366):\n  - Connects to HTTP SSE endpoint at `/api/runs/{runID}/stream`\n  - Parses JSON log entries\n  - Color codes by type: blue=status, green=llm, default=script\n  - Terminates on \"event: done\"\n\n#### gRPC Log Streaming (`/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`, lines 458-634):\n\n1. **StreamLogs** (lines 458-555):\n   - Primary entry point for CLI log requests\n   - If no step/type filter:\n     - Tries to read `full.log` first (preferred unified log)\n     - Falls back to capture-based streaming\n     - Sends step_started, step_completed, run_completed entries\n   - Supports filtering by step and/or type\n\n2. **streamFilteredLogs** (lines 559-634):\n   - Filters logs by step name and/or type\n   - Uses LogStore index for fast lookup when available\n   - Falls back to file path conventions\n   - Reads from indexed file paths and sends content\n\n### 5. **Key Data Structures**\n\n- **StepExecution** (`/workspace/internal/domain/run.go`):\n  - StepName, Result, StartedAt, CompletedAt, Logs, GitRef\n\n- **LogLine** (`/workspace/internal/logstream/logstream.go`):\n  - JSON: Timestamp, Type, Content\n\n- **LogFileEntry** (`/workspace/internal/ports/store.go`):\n  - Database index of log files with paths and metadata\n\n- **LogEntry** (gRPC proto):\n  - Type, StepName, Result, Message, Timestamp\n\n### 6. **File Locations**\n\nAll log output is stored in: `{projectDir}/.cloche/{runID}/output/`\n- `full.log` - unified master log with all entries\n- `{stepName}.log` - per-step script output\n- `llm-{stepName}.log` - Claude Code agent output\n- `container.log` - internal Docker container logs (not indexed)\n\n### 7. **Flow Summary**\n\n**Writing**: Container execution → captured to files → logstream.Writer appends to full.log → indexLogFiles() indexes in SQLite\n\n**Display (Web UI)**:\n- Active: SSE broadcasts from logstream.Broadcaster → run_detail.html appends DOM elements\n- Completed: full.log read line-by-line → SSE stream → run_detail.html displays\n\n**Display (CLI)**:\n- gRPC StreamLogs RPC → reads from indexed log files → LogEntry messages → pretty printed\n\n**Absolute paths to key files:**\n- `/workspace/internal/logstream/logstream.go` - log file writing\n- `/workspace/internal/logstream/broadcaster.go` - live streaming\n- `/workspace/internal/logparse/parse.go` - Claude Code stream parsing\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` - web API endpoints\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html` - log viewer UI\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` - gRPC streaming and indexing\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go` - log database persistence\n- `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go` - LogStore interface\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` - CLI log commands\n- `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto` - gRPC service definition"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a650ab48781d53c2c (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 68133\ntool_uses: 37\nduration_ms: 60118</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"681eabd5-00bc-42d3-9384-f3323237aaa3","uuid":"a98eb0ec-b237-4136-8dcd-d95bc63b336d","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Find all code related to displaying run logs/history in this project. Look for:\n1. How logs are stored and retrieved (logparse, capture, etc.)\n2. How logs are displayed in the web UI (templates, handlers)\n3. How logs are displayed in the CLI\n4. Any existing log parsing code\n\nSearch thoroughly in internal/adapters/web/, internal/logparse/, cmd/cloche/, internal/domain/, internal/ports/, and templates.","agentId":"a650ab48781d53c2c","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a complete picture. Let me create a comprehensive report of all code related to displaying run logs and history.\n\n## Summary of Log Display Code in Cloche\n\nI've thoroughly searched the codebase for all code related to displaying run logs and history. Here's a complete breakdown:\n\n### 1. **Log Storage and Retrieval**\n\n#### Log Writing/Persistence:\n- **File**: `/workspace/internal/logstream/logstream.go`\n  - `Writer` struct with `Log()` method writes timestamped, type-prefixed log entries to `.cloche/output/full.log`\n  - Format: `[timestamp] [type] content` (one entry per line)\n  - Supports three entry types: `TypeStatus`, `TypeScript`, `TypeLLM`\n  - Thread-safe with mutex locks\n\n#### Log Storage Interface and Implementation:\n- **Ports** (`/workspace/internal/ports/store.go`):\n  - `LogStore` interface with methods:\n    - `SaveLogFile()` - indexes a log file entry\n    - `GetLogFiles()` - retrieves all log files for a run\n    - `GetLogFilesByStep()` - retrieves logs for a specific step\n    - `GetLogFileByType()` - retrieves logs of a specific type (full/script/llm)\n  - `LogFileEntry` struct with fields: ID, RunID, StepName, FileType, FilePath, FileSize, CreatedAt\n\n- **Implementation** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go`):\n  - SQLite database with `log_files` table\n  - `SaveLogFile()` at line 301 - inserts into log_files table\n  - `GetLogFiles()` at line 311 - queries all logs for a run\n  - `GetLogFilesByStep()` at line 322 - queries logs by run and step name\n  - `GetLogFileByType()` at line 333 - queries logs by type\n  - Helper function `scanLogFiles()` at line 344 parses query results\n\n#### Log File Indexing:\n- **gRPC Server** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`, lines 704-757):\n  - `indexLogFiles()` function scans output directory after run completes\n  - Categorizes files:\n    - `full.log` → fileType=\"full\" (complete unified log)\n    - `llm-*.log` → fileType=\"llm\" (Claude Code output)\n    - `<step>.log` → fileType=\"script\" (script/command output)\n    - `container.log` is skipped (internal use only)\n  - Creates index entries for database persistence\n\n### 2. **Log Parsing**\n\n- **File**: `/workspace/internal/logparse/parse.go`\n  - `FormatStreamJSON()` - converts raw Claude Code stream-json output to human-readable text\n  - Parses event types: `content_block_start`, `content_block_delta`, `content_block_stop`, `message_stop`, `result`\n  - Extracts text content and tool names from stream\n  - `IsStreamJSON()` - detects if content is Claude Code stream-json format\n  - Returns original if parsing fails (graceful fallback)\n\n### 3. **Web UI Display**\n\n#### Log Streaming for Active Runs:\n- **Broadcaster** (`/workspace/internal/logstream/broadcaster.go`):\n  - `Broadcaster` struct manages real-time log distribution\n  - `Subscribe()` - clients subscribe to a run's log stream\n  - `Publish()` - broadcasts LogLine to all subscribers with non-blocking delivery\n  - `Finish()` - closes all subscriber channels when run completes\n  - `LogLine` struct: Timestamp, Type, Content\n\n#### Handler Functions (`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`):\n\n1. **handleAPIStream** (lines 721-780):\n   - Server-Sent Events (SSE) endpoint at `/api/runs/{id}/stream`\n   - For active runs: subscribes to logBroadcast and streams live updates\n   - For completed runs: reads archived full.log file\n   - Sends \"done\" event with final run state\n\n2. **streamFullLog** (lines 786-802):\n   - Reads `.cloche/{runID}/output/full.log` line by line\n   - Parses \"[timestamp] [type] content\" format via regex\n   - Converts to LogLine JSON and sends as SSE events\n\n3. **parseFullLogLine** (lines 805-819):\n   - Regex: `^\\[([^\\]]+)\\] \\[([^\\]]+)\\] (.*)$`\n   - Extracts timestamp, type, content from full.log lines\n\n4. **handleAPIStepOutput** (lines 564-639):\n   - JSON endpoint at `/api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output`\n   - Retrieves step-specific logs with optional filtering by type\n   - Priority: log index → file path conventions → live docker logs\n   - Calls `logparse.FormatStreamJSON()` unless format=raw\n   - Log file lookup order:\n     - `{outputDir}/llm-{step}.log` (if type==\"llm\")\n     - `{outputDir}/{step}.log` (per-step output)\n     - `{outputDir}/container.log` (fallback)\n     - Live Docker logs from container if still running\n\n#### Templates (`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/`):\n\n1. **run_detail.html** (lines 1-238):\n   - Log viewer section: `<div id=\"log-viewer\">` with pre-formatted content\n   - Step execution table with clickable rows\n   - Real-time log status badge showing \"Live\" or \"Complete\"\n   - JavaScript:\n     - Connects to SSE stream at `/api/runs/{runID}/stream`\n     - `appendLogLine()` - adds log entries to DOM with type-based CSS classes\n     - Auto-scroll enabled while at bottom; disabled when scrolled up\n     - Poll updates for steps every 2 seconds during active runs\n     - Click handlers for expandable step output rows\n     - Fetches step output from `/api/runs/{runID}/steps/{step}/output`\n\n2. **runs.html** (lines 1-106):\n   - Lists all runs with state, workflow, started/completed times\n   - Truncated error messages (80 chars)\n   - Project filter dropdown\n   - Polls `/api/runs` every 3 seconds for updates\n\n3. **layout.html** and **projects.html**:\n   - Mini run history (recent dots with color-coded states)\n   - Project health indicators\n\n### 4. **CLI Log Display**\n\n#### Command: `cloche logs` (`/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go`, lines 223-304):\n\n- Subcommand: `logs <run-id> [--step <name>] [--type <full|script|llm>] [--follow]`\n- **Without --follow**: \n  - Calls gRPC `StreamLogs()` RPC\n  - Streams LogEntry messages\n  - Handles types: \"step_started\", \"step_completed\", \"run_completed\", \"full_log\", \"*_log\"\n- **With --follow** (`cmdLogsFollow`, lines 306-366):\n  - Connects to HTTP SSE endpoint at `/api/runs/{runID}/stream`\n  - Parses JSON log entries\n  - Color codes by type: blue=status, green=llm, default=script\n  - Terminates on \"event: done\"\n\n#### gRPC Log Streaming (`/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`, lines 458-634):\n\n1. **StreamLogs** (lines 458-555):\n   - Primary entry point for CLI log requests\n   - If no step/type filter:\n     - Tries to read `full.log` first (preferred unified log)\n     - Falls back to capture-based streaming\n     - Sends step_started, step_completed, run_completed entries\n   - Supports filtering by step and/or type\n\n2. **streamFilteredLogs** (lines 559-634):\n   - Filters logs by step name and/or type\n   - Uses LogStore index for fast lookup when available\n   - Falls back to file path conventions\n   - Reads from indexed file paths and sends content\n\n### 5. **Key Data Structures**\n\n- **StepExecution** (`/workspace/internal/domain/run.go`):\n  - StepName, Result, StartedAt, CompletedAt, Logs, GitRef\n\n- **LogLine** (`/workspace/internal/logstream/logstream.go`):\n  - JSON: Timestamp, Type, Content\n\n- **LogFileEntry** (`/workspace/internal/ports/store.go`):\n  - Database index of log files with paths and metadata\n\n- **LogEntry** (gRPC proto):\n  - Type, StepName, Result, Message, Timestamp\n\n### 6. **File Locations**\n\nAll log output is stored in: `{projectDir}/.cloche/{runID}/output/`\n- `full.log` - unified master log with all entries\n- `{stepName}.log` - per-step script output\n- `llm-{stepName}.log` - Claude Code agent output\n- `container.log` - internal Docker container logs (not indexed)\n\n### 7. **Flow Summary**\n\n**Writing**: Container execution → captured to files → logstream.Writer appends to full.log → indexLogFiles() indexes in SQLite\n\n**Display (Web UI)**:\n- Active: SSE broadcasts from logstream.Broadcaster → run_detail.html appends DOM elements\n- Completed: full.log read line-by-line → SSE stream → run_detail.html displays\n\n**Display (CLI)**:\n- gRPC StreamLogs RPC → reads from indexed log files → LogEntry messages → pretty printed\n\n**Absolute paths to key files:**\n- `/workspace/internal/logstream/logstream.go` - log file writing\n- `/workspace/internal/logstream/broadcaster.go` - live streaming\n- `/workspace/internal/logparse/parse.go` - Claude Code stream parsing\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` - web API endpoints\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html` - log viewer UI\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` - gRPC streaming and indexing\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go` - log database persistence\n- `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go` - LogStore interface\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` - CLI log commands\n- `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto` - gRPC service definition"}],"totalDurationMs":60118,"totalTokens":68133,"totalToolUseCount":37,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1343,"cache_read_input_tokens":64223,"output_tokens":2567,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1343},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
